abstract: The F.C.C. will vote on Tuesday on a proposal to make a disputed chunk of radio spectrum available for public use.
snippet: The F.C.C. will vote on Tuesday on a proposal to make a disputed chunk of radio spectrum available for public use.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO  Tuesday marks the end of a battle that has lasted for more than two years, with each side predicting apocalyptic consequences should it lose.

headline.main: Airwaves Battle Pits Dolly Parton Against Google
headline.print_headline: Tech Giants Draw a Foe: Dolly Parton

abstract: Google and Yahoo have sent the Justice Department a revised search advertising deal aimed at appeasing antitrust regulators who have raised concerns about the original deal, people briefed on the matter told DealBook.
lead_paragraph: Google and Yahoo have sent the Justice Department a revised search advertising deal aimed at appeasing antitrust regulators who have raised concerns about the original deal, people briefed on the matter told DealBook.

headline.main: Google and Yahoo Revise Their Search Advertising Pact

abstract: The companies have offered to narrow the scope of the deal in a last-minute effort to win the approval of the Justice Department.
snippet: The companies have offered to narrow the scope of the deal in a last-minute effort to win the approval of the Justice Department.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO  Google and Yahoo have offered to significantly narrow the scope of a planned advertising partnership in a last-minute effort to win the approval of the Justice Department, which is scrutinizing the deal for its effect on competition, a person briefed on the revised plan said on Monday.

headline.main: Yahoo and Google Offer to Revise Ad Partnership
headline.print_headline: Google and Yahoo Revamp Ad Plan for Regulators
